<article>
    <h3 class="card-title">Does Your Car Need Auto Repair Services?</h3>
    <p>Even if you’ve been driving for decades, it can be tough to tell if your vehicle needs auto repair services.</p>
    <p>Luckily, there are a few telltale signs that your car needs to be inspected by an ASE-certified mechanic.</p>
    <p>Is your car stalling or struggling to start? Is your check engine light (CEL) illuminated on your dashboard?</p>
    <p>Or is your CEL flickering? Call the automotive repair experts at JD Automotive Service in Fort Worth, Texas, today.</p>
    <p>For over 16 years, we have been helping our customers with their automotive service and maintenance needs including brake repair, and more.</p>
    <p>A few other red flags that your car needs to be looked at by a qualified mechanic include excessive exhaust smoke, smoke coming from beneath the hood,
        reduced stopping power, any noticeable leaks, poor gas mileage, a shaking steering wheel, slipping gears, or loud grinding or squealing sounds coming from the brakes.</p>
    <p>If you notice any of these issues, call JD Automotive Service now. We will quickly get to work diagnosing and repairing your vehicle.</p>
</article>

